    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Continuous tone color prints created by the thermal development of light-sensitive materials to transfer a latent image onto print media. The process is marketed as 'Pictrography' by Fuji Photo Film Co. Ltd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051051/Jürgens, The Digital Print (2009)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051049/Baldwin and Jürgens, Looking at Photographs (2009)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afdrukken met een continu kleurenspectrum, gemaakt door de thermische ontwikkeling van lichtgevoelige materialen om een afbeelding op een afdrukmedium over te brengen. Deze techniek is op de markt gebracht als ���Pictrography' door Fuji Photo Film Co. Ltd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以光敏材料之熱成像來把潛影轉印至印刷媒材上，創造出連續調彩色印刷。該照相製版術由富士軟片股份有限公司(Fuji Photo Film Co. Ltd)以「高品質數位影像輸出機」(Pictrography)上市行銷。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
